item.name: Markets
item.description:
APIs for managing markets.
  • Please provide the market attribute in all APIs related to in Snake_Case.
    Examples:BTC-USDT, ETH-IRT and ...
  • You still can provide market attribute in PascalCase but beware that the Accountancy module would not work properly and as expected.

request.description: This endpoint will deliver an object of all markets sorted by descending order of @created_at.
This endpoint will store a new market.
This endpoint will deliver the market's statistics (Ticker) of last 24 hour.

This endpoint will deliver the market's candlestick data on requested timeframe.
Available timeframes are: 1W, 1M, 1Y

variable.description: Defines the queue of order, if it's true, only the virtual orders would be the outcome.

request.description: This endpoint will deliver the most recent orderbook of market in descending order of time.
This endpoint will accept an array of markets and search database for proper results.
This endpoint will deliver the market's most recent trades in descending order of time.
This endpoint will deliver the very single object of specified market by it's name.
This endpoint will update an existing market.

item.name: Orders
item.description:
APIs for managing orders.
  • All order id's in url parameters should be internal_order_id property of order.

request.description: This endpoint will deliver an object of all orders sorted by descending order of @created_at.
This endpoint will store a new order.
This endpoint will cancel the order if it's cancelable.
This endpoint will deliver the very single object of specified order by it's ID.

item.name: Settings
item.description: APIs for handling settings of application.

request.description: This endpoint will deliver all settings that have been stored in database.
